.TH EYEMOUSE 1 "2026" "tobii4c" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
eyemouse \- realtime eye controlled mouse for Tobii Eye Tracker 4C on Linux/X11

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B eyemouse

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B eyemouse
provides realtime gaze controlled mouse interaction using the
Tobii Eye Tracker 4C under Linux/X11.

The current stable runtime uses:

- barycentric triangle mesh calibrationsh calibration
- 3x3 calibration mesh
- low latency smoothing
- X11 cursor control
- realtime Tobii gaze tracking

The runtime maps gaze coordinates onto desktop cursousing barycentric triangle mesh interpolationerpolation derived from fullscreen calibration samples.om fullscreen calibration samples.

.SH REQUIREMENTS
Required:

- Linux
- X11 session
- Tobii Eye Tracker 4C
- Tobii Stream Engine runtime

Wayland is currently unsupported.

Check current session type:

.nf
$ echo $XDG_SESSION_TYPE
x11
.fi

.SH CALIBRATION FILE
Calibration data is loaded from:

.nf
~/.local/tobii_4c/calx11.conf
.fi

The stable runtime currently expects a 3x3 calibration mesh.

Example:

.nf
0.052524 0.075656 0.050000 0.050000
0.498691 0.050737 0.500000 0.050000
0.941116 0.014396 0.950000 0.050000
.fi

Format:

.nf
raw_x raw_y target_x target_y
.fi

Meaning:

- raw_x/raw_y:
  measured Tobii gaze coordinates

- target_x/target_y:
  expected normalized screen coordinates

.SH RUNTIME PIPELINE
Runtime processing:

.nf
raw Tobii gaze
    -> affine calibration correction
    -> smoothing
    -> edge stabilization
    -> X11 cursor mapping
    -> XWarpPointer
.fi
e performs local barycentric triangle mesh interpolation.

Conceptually:

.nf
triangle selectioon
.fi

This improves:

- fullscreen reachability
- corner precision
- edge access
- asymmetric distortion

.SH EDGE BEHAVIOR
Eye trackers are nonlinear devices.

Typical behavior:

.nf
center:
    stable

edges:
    compressed

corners:
    less accurate
.fi

Local barycentric triangle interpolation compensatExample runtime output:

.nf
Mouse 1365 150
.fi

Meaning:

- cursor x position
- cursor y position

.SH FILES
.nf
~/.local/tobii_4c/calx11.conf
.fi

.SH LIMITATIONS
Current limitations:

- X11 only
- no Wayland support
- no full 3D reprojection
- no active headpose correction
- experimental advanced geometry support

.SH EXPERIMENTAL FEATURES
Experimental runtime branches may contain:

- bootstrap geometry import
- C12 runtime
- projective warp
- homography mapping
- adaptive mesh refinement
- head compensated gaze mapping

These are not fully active in the stable runtime.

